        "Data": [
          "<h1>Applies to</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>PHP</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n  <h1>What to Do</h1>\r\n  <p>Use PHP session management, instead of writing your own.</p>\r\n  <h1>Why</h1>\r\n  <p>The framework works on a lower level than the application and is therefore better suited to provide session management. PHP offers mature and simple to use session management functionality.</p>\r\n  <h1>How</h1>\r\n  <p>Please, refer to the link to the PHP manual below for thorough documentation of PHP session management functionality.</p>\r\n  <h1>Additional Resources</h1>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>For information about PHP session management, see <a href=\"http://www.php.net/manual/en/book.session.php\">http://www.php.net/manual/en/book.session.php</a></li>\r\n  </ul>"
